title: Statutory Exemption, Bureau of Engineering report and Motion (McOsker - Raman) relative to funding allocation, lease, change in service provider and continued use for a period of approximately up to three years for the bridge housing/low barrier navigation center facility located at 2316 Imperial Highway in Council District 15, for those experiencing homelessness; and determination that the projects are statutorily exempt from the California Environmental Quality Act (CEQA) under Public Resources Code (PRC) Section 21080.27.5, applicable to low barrier navigation centers and Government Code Section 8698.4(a)(4), governing homeless shelter projects under a shelter crisis declaration.
